Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Dating: NEW KINGDOM (not after); NAPATAN PERIOD (not before)
Name: Ring
Description: Simple, slightly misshapen metal ring. The two extremities overlap for about 1 cm. Originally welded together, these extremities are now detached from one another (only a few white traces remain of the binder which was originally used to weld the two metal ends together).
